SIMPLE: cupbearer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cupbearer
<hw>Cup"bear`er</hw> <pr>(-b⟦acir⟧r`⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>One whose office it is to fill and hand the cups at an
entertainment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Antiq.)</fld> <def>One of the attendants of a
prince or noble, permanently charged with the performance of this office
for his master.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧I was the king's
<xex>cupbearer</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Neh. i. 11.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cupboard</ent>⟦br⟧
